What is difference between path and classpath variables?
- The PATH is the system variable that  is used to locate JDK binaries like "java" or "javac" command used to run java program and compile java source file.
- Classpath is a variable  in the Java Virtual Machine or the Java compiler that specifies the location of user-defined classes and packages.
What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
An Interface class in java is a blueprint for class. An abstract class is a hybrid class having both abstract and non-abstract methods. An Interface has only abstract  method  that has definition  but no implementation. Interface class Interface class is public variables are private and static by default. But in abstract class, we can use all the access modifiers., Interface uses ‘implements’ keyword ,abstract uses ‘extends’ keyword.
Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
what is Access Specifier?
Access specifier defines the scope of class attributes
