What is the difference between JDK and JVM?
-JVM is Java Virtual Machine that actually runs Java bytecode.JDK is Java Developer Kit that  is  you need to compile Java source code.
What is the difference between JVM and JRE?
JRE is a software bundle that allows Java program to run, whereas JVM is an environment for executing bytecode.
What is compile time and run time?
